---
import Button from "./button.astro";
---

<section class="bg-gray-200">
  <div class="py-8 lg:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl px-4 md:px-8 mx-auto text-gray-500 sm:text-lg">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-800">
        Why{" "}
        <span class="font-extrabold text-primary">Stained Glass?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 font-light text-gray-900">
        Granite withheld the test of time because it is impervious to weather
        and normal wear in the cemeteries. Unfortunately, the paint or stain
        used to enhance the letters, numbers, and designs on today&apos;s
        granite, have a life expectancy of 2 to maybe 8 years.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4 font-medium text-gray-900">
        Simply put, stained glass will never fade. We installed our first sample
        gravestone twelve years ago. We&apos;ve tested our inlays to extremes
        that monuments will never face. In some ways, our finished product is
        even tougher than the carved granite itself.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/product"
        class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-800 inline-flex items-center font-medium"
      >
        <Button>
          Learn More About Our Glass
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            fill="currentColor"
            class="w-5 h-5 ml-2"
          >
            <path
              fill-rule="evenodd"
              d="M3 10a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h10.638L10.23 5.29a.75.75 0 1 1 1.04-1.08l5.5 5.25a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.08l-5.5 5.25a.75.75 0 1 1-1.04-1.08l4.158-3.96H3.75A.75.75 0 0 1 3 10Z"
              clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
          </svg>
        </Button>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
